edu.rit.util

Class DList<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.rit.util.DList<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - List item data type.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Streamable

    public class DList<T>
extends Object
implements Streamable
    Class DList provides a list of items stored in a doubly-linked list. Each item is contained in a DListEntry.

    Operations take constant time unless otherwise specified. n is the number of items stored in the list.

      • find

        public DListEntry<T> find(T item)
        Find the first entry in this list that contains the given item. This involves a linear scan of the list entries from beginning to end; the returned value is the first entry encountered whose item is equal to the given item, as determined by the item's equals() method; if there is no such entry, null is returned. Time: O(n).
        Parameters:
        item - Item.
        Returns:
        Entry containing matching item, or null if none.

      • find

        public DListEntry<T> find(Predicate<T> predicate)
        Find the first entry in this list that contains an item for which the given predicate is true. This involves a linear scan of the list entries from beginning to end; the returned value is the first entry encountered for which the predicate's test() method returns true; if there is no such entry, null is returned. Time: O(n).
        Parameters:
        predicate - Predicate.
        Returns:
        Entry containing matching item, or null if none.

      • forEachItemDo

        public <R> R forEachItemDo(ActionResult<T,R> action)
        Perform the given action on each item in this list and return a result. For each item in this list from beginning to end, the given action's run() method is called, passing in the item. After all the items have been processed, the given action's result() method is called, and its result is returned. Time: O(n).

        Warning: If the action adds items to or removes items from the list, the forEachItemDo() method's behavior is not specified.

        Type Parameters:
        R - Result data type.
        Parameters:
        action - Action.
        Returns:
        Result of processing all the list items.

      • removeEachItemIf

        public void removeEachItemIf(Predicate<T> predicate)
        Evaluate the given predicate on, and possibly remove, each item in this list. For each item in this list from beginning to end, the given predicate's test() method is called, passing in the item. If the test() method returns true, the item is removed from this list. Time: O(n).

        Warning: If the predicate adds items to or removes items from the list, other than by returning true, the removeEachItemIf() method's behavior is not specified.

        Parameters:
        predicate - Predicate.

      • toArray

        public T[] toArray(T[] array)
        Store this list's items in the given array. The first item is stored at index 0, the second item at index 1, and so on. The number of array elements set is array.length. If this list contains fewer than array.length items, the remaining array elements are set to null. Time: O(n).
        Parameters:
        array - Array in which to store items.
        Returns:
        The given array is returned.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - (unchecked exception) Thrown if array is null.

      • toArray

        public T[] toArray(T[] array,
          int off,
          int len)
        Store this list's items in the given array. The first item is stored at index off, the second item at index off+1, and so on. The number of array elements set is len. If this list contains fewer than len items, the remaining array elements are set to null. Time: O(n).
        Parameters:
        array - Array in which to store items.
        off - Index at which to store first item.
        len - Number of items to store.
        Returns:
        The given array is returned.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - (unchecked exception) Thrown if array is null.
        IndexOutOfBoundsException - (unchecked exception) Thrown if off < 0, len < 0, or off+len > array.length.
